cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

The paper deals with modeling and recognition of surgical activities using computer vision techniques, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of spatial temporal graph representations and convolutional networks indicates that it may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the use of video data and gesture recognition suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
